     So[0m[2m the fixes[0m[2m are:[0m[2m
     1.[0m[2m In `[0m[2mjob_queue[0m[2m.py`,[0m[2m remove[0m[2m the `[0m[2mawait asyncio[0m[2m.sleep([0m[2m0.[0m[2m01)`[0m[2m from[0m[2m `de[0m[2mqueue`,[0m[2m or better[0m[2m yet,[0m[2m change status[0m[2m to "[0m[2mprocessing"[0m[2m *before[0m[2m* yielding[0m[2m control[0m[2m. But[0m[2m since[0m[2m we're[0m[2m in async[0m[2m, any[0m[2m await[0m[2m gives[0m[2m a[0m[2m chance for[0m[2m inter[0m[2mleaving[0m[2m. The[0m[2m simplest fix[0m[2m is to[0m[2m set `[0m[2mjob[0m[2m["status[0m[2m"] =[0m[2m "processing[0m[2m"` before[0m[2m the[0m[2m `await[0m[2m asyncio.sleep[0m[2m(0[0m[2m.01[0m[2m)[0m[2m`.
     
