**Fix summary:**

**Bug 1 — Duplicate processing (race condition)** in `job_queue.py:22-26`:
The `await asyncio.sleep(0.01)` was sandwiched between "find pending job" and "set status to processing." In asyncio, an `await` is a context-switch point, so every concurrent worker slipped through and grabbed the same job before any of them updated the status. Moved `job["status"] = "processing"` to happen *before* the `await`.

**Bug 2 — Vanishing failures (missing failure notification)** in `worker.py:18-19`:
When a job raised an exception, the worker caught it and logged it but never called back into the queue. The job stayed in `"processing"` forever, bypassing retry logic and never reaching `"failed"`. Added `queue.fail(job["id"], str(e))` so the queue can track retries and eventually mark the job failed.
